practitioner.about:
Dr. Hussam Mohamad Al Trabulsi is a surgeon who specialises in bariatric surgery and laparoscopic surgery, with a degree from Syria, and certifications from the UK and EU. He holds a Certificate of General Surgery Specialty from the Syrian Ministry of Health. He has also qualified as a member of the the Royal College of Surgeon (MRCS), Edinburgh, UK. He also has a European Board of Surgery qualification.

Dr. Al Trabulsi has worked at the Zulekha Hospital in Dubai and the Al Die Surgical Hospital in Syria. He is a member of a number of professional associations related to his specialisation. These include the the Syrian Association of Surgeons (SAS ), the Syrian Association of Laparoscopic Surgery (SALS), the Emirates Medical Association (EMA), the Emirates Association of Metabolic and Bariatric Surgery, the International Federation of Obesity Surgery (IFSO) and the Emirates Society of Metabolic and Bariatric Surgery (ESMBS).

Dr. Hussam Mohamad Al Trabulsi performs a number of bariatric and advanced laparoscopy procedures. He uses laparoscopic techniques to carry out classic gastric bypass, mini gastric bypass, sleeve gastrectomy, adjustable gastric banding, gastric plication, hiatus hernia repair, and cholecystectomy. He also performs revision bariatric surgery.

Dr. Al Trabulsi makes time from his busy work schedule to pursue his love for reading and football. He speaks Arabic and English.
